  <refnamediv>
    <refname>impixel</refname>
    <refpurpose>Return selected pixel coordinates and values</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Syntax</title>
   <synopsis>
   [xc,yc,pixval] = impixel(S);
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>S :</term>
      <listitem><para> Image matrix in Scilab</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>xc :</term>
      <listitem><para> x-coordinates for the selected points</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>yc :</term>
      <listitem><para> y-coordinates for the selected points</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>pixval :</term>
      <listitem><para> Correspond pixels' values</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
This function provides interactive way to select the points on an image
and returned with the locations and pixels values. Multiple points could
be selected with left mouse click and the last point should be selected
with the right mouse click.
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
S = imread(fullpath(getIPCVpath() + "/images/balloons.png"));
impixel(S);

   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>

